Cell.Text: You're not one of my workers. What are you doing here?
[S] Oh, yes. Weylin. Bastard could have at least gone crazy after we made our silver quota.

Node.Caption: MS01MulushAttackTopic: I'm looking into the market attack.

Cell.Text: [S] You hard of hearing? I run this smelter. And I'm late meeting our silver quota. What do you want?
[S] Well then, look. Look all you want. And when you're done looking, maybe we can get some work done.
Whatever you want to know, I don't care. I run a smelter. That's it.
[S] Fine. I did notice something odd last time we handed out the pay. Little extra slip of paper for Weylin. Took it right to his room after he got it.
No. I don't.
[S] For that amount, I can. Fine. I did notice something odd last time we handed out the pay. | Little extra slip of paper for Weylin. Took it right to his room after he got it.
No.
[S] Hold, on there. I think I just remembered something. The last time we handed out pay. | Little extra slip of paper for Weylin. Took it right to his room.
You better start caring. (Brawl)
[S] G|<<Shared>> I don't have to take this from the likes of you.
Hmph.
Every other day, seems one of the laborers runs off in the hills saying he'll join the Forsworn. | You don't like the Nords? Fine. But pledging your whole life to killing them? That's just dumb.
Do you know anything about the Forsworn?
Don't get involved in that nonsense. Just want to work.
Tell me about the Forsworn.
We've lost a lot of good people to that damn crusade. Drive out the Nords, they say. Well, the Nord ain't driven out.

Node.Caption: MS01MulushForswornTopic: What do you know about the Forsworn?

Cell.Text: What? No. Thonar Silver-Blood owns it. He owns everything in Markarth. | But he hands all the paperwork over to Nepos the Nose to finish. That old man's back is heavy with burden.
Who else works here?

Me and Hathrasil mostly. Mulush barks at us all day, but I wouldn't call that honest work. | A few people in the Warrens used to work here. Degaine broke some bones a while back, Eltrys quit. Cairine is too sick.
Who's in charge of the smelter?
Mulush. Big Orc fella. Can't miss him.
Really should talk to Mulush if you have a problem with one of the workers.
The Forsworn? That's right. I'll say it. We all knew. Even that fat-headed, slave-driving Mulush knew. Just ask him about it. | Bah. Another honest man lost in all this madness. And for what?
[S] You want Garvey. He handles the keys for the Warrens. About the only thing that disease-riddled native is good for.

Node.Caption: MS01MulushWeylinKeyTopic: Do you have the key to Weylin's room?

Cell.Text: It's where you go if you can't afford a room anywhere else. About the time they opened the mines, someone got the idea to throw beds in here. | Laborers. The sick. The lame. We're all here.
[S] Oh yes. I know everyone who sleeps in the Warrens. Kind of the one who passes the keys around. | I guess someone else will be taking his room, now.
Sorry, but you don't exactly belong here.

Node.Caption: MS01GarveyGiveKeyTopic: I need the key to Weylin's room.

Cell.Text: [S] Trust is hard to come by here, but all right.
No. It's not. Trust me.
[S] Welcome to the Warrens.
No, I don't think so.
[S] Now don't get all upset. Here. Take it.
And I wasn't stuttering. No key.
Right.
